## üé® Typography System

### Fonts
Use **Roboto Flex** (preferred), Roboto Serif, or Roboto Mono with the following variable axes:
- `weight`: controls thickness
- `grade`: optical weight (subtle visual weight)
- `width`: horizontal stretch of characters
- `slant`: italic behavior
- `optical size`: adjusts detail/resolution based on size

### Roles
Define every text block by one of five roles:
| Role      | Use Case                               | Notes |
|-----------|----------------------------------------|-------|
| `Display` | Large screens / marketing hero         | Use expressive/handwritten for emotional pull |
| `Headline`| Short, high-emphasis lines             | Great for section titles, overlays |
| `Title`   | Medium importance, compact layout      | Good for cards, modals |
| `Body`    | Paragraphs, readable at all sizes      | Avoid decorative fonts |
| `Label`   | Small UI like buttons, captions        | Prioritize clarity over style |

